import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['longitude'], data['latitude'], s=10, alpha=0.5)
    plt.xlabel('Longitude')
    plt.ylabel('Latitude')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of latitude and longitude across the dataset?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    airports_per_country = data.groupby('country')['iata'].count().sort_values(ascending=False)
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))
    ax.bar(airports_per_country.index, airports_per_country.values, color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Country')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Airports')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of airports across different countries?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.tight_layout()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('state')['iata'].count().reset_index()
    data = data.sort_values(by='iata', ascending=False)
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))
    ax.bar(data['state'], data['iata'], color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('State/Province')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Airports')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of airports across different states/provinces?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.tight_layout()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
from wordcloud import WordCloud

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    airport_names = data.groupby(['city'])['name'].apply(list).reset_index(name='airport_names')
    airport_names['airport_names'] = airport_names['airport_names'].apply(lambda x: ' '.join(x))
    wordcloud = WordCloud(width=800, height=400, background_color='white', max_words=200, colormap='Set2').generate(' '.join(airport_names['airport_names']))
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 10))
    plt.imshow(wordcloud, interpolation='bilinear')
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airport names across different cities?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
from wordcloud import WordCloud

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    wc = WordCloud(width=800, height=400, max_words=200, background_color='white').generate_from_frequencies(data.groupby('country')['name'].value_counts())
    plt.figure(figsize=(20,10))
    plt.imshow(wc, interpolation='bilinear')
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airport names across different countries?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
